sparkasse league, also known as s league is a top-level regional handball league that features teams from bosnia and herzegovina, croatia, montenegro, serbia, macedonia, poland and slovakia. first season of competition will start at august 2011. the league exists alongside scaled-down versions of domestic leagues in each country (bih handball championship, croatian first league, macedonian first league, first handball league of montenegro, polish extraleague, serbian first league and slovakian handball extraleague). except bosnia and herzegovina and slovakia, there are two teams from every country. members of first season of regional sparkasse league are rk bosna, rk borac, hrk izviđač, rk zagreb, rk nexe, rk metalurg skopje, hc vardar pro – skopje